reviews_data.review_text: Easily some of the best coffee in charlotte. Always so dense and fresh and full bodied, and super nice baristas. I spend way too much money here!
Small cafe with pretty good coffee.

We love the Enderly community. Michelle, Tony, Kimoy and the entire team are amazing! The coffee is top quality and the staff is super friendly and helpful. They support and uplift other small businesses.  We drive across town every weekend just to get this delicious coffee.
Enderly Coffee is just a complete gem of Charlotte! Proudly local, hardworking and most importantly: fantastic products. Love their coffee!

I cannot rate the actual brick and mortar Enderly Coffee company because I've never visited the establishment. But I bought a bag of their Honduras Coffee beans from a grocery store and was extremely disappointed. It's honestly the worst Coffee I've ever bought to make at home, especially when I'm grinding the beans fresh myself. It has NO flavor, I even tried using a large amount thinking maybe I didn't use enough, but it didn't matter. It was like drinking warm water with my sweet cream, creamer I adore. That's never happened before.  It's a medium roast and I expected it to be really good considering it's roasted locally in Charlotte.  I moved out of Charlotte in 1985 & I live an hour away. I thought this would be great since Charlotte is so close and should be really fresh and wonderful. Sadly it was not. They may have other Coffee beans that are better and hopefully stronger so it actually tastes like coffee. But I doubt I'll be purchasing this companies products again.  I should have known that when the grocery store marked down all Enderly Coffee products on clearance that apparently weren't selling and I  bet you this is why because it seriously sucks. I threw the rest away because it wasn't worthy salvaging and maybe mixing with other Coffee, because I tried that too. What a waste of money and time. I worked in the restaurant business for 30 yrs and traveled alot as well and this is truly the worst Coffee I've ever had because it doesn't taste like you're drinking coffee at all. And it's not just my opinion, relatives and friends that I had visiting and served it to agreed with me. I was a little embarrassed honestly. I dumped it down the sink and made my other brand  of coffee instead. Very inconvenient when you are serving breakfast to a house full of relatives visiting from out of town.

The place looks nondescript from outside, tucked along several homes turned into small businesses. But once you step inside, it’s very lively and cozy. The staff or friendly. The latte with salted maple was awesome. There is a small parking on the backside. Otherwise you may have to park on the street.
We had an event here at it went amazing! Such a great atmosphere and location!
Best coffee in Charlotte!
Great service and the coffee are great and well served.
Amazing drinks and food !!
I am a regular around here, we just had a networking event here. The whole staff was great, and Michelle is the best :)
What a total treat!!  Thank you!
Such a cute coffee shop! Biscoff cookie latte is 10/10. Really nice staff too! Stop here next time you're in Charlotte.

Got a hot chai latte, coffee lemonade, cherry cinnamon roll, and almond muffin- no chai flavor just milky with the barest taste of chai (like how sparkling waters taste like a hint of fruit burp) , coffee lemonade is exactly what it sounds like. Microwave available to heat up your pastries yourself. Cute place, overall okay.
An awesome roaster. Videos were all time high at their shop and the coffee was outstanding. Loved my espresso! Quiet spot but with great energy - everything roasted in house. Check them out!
Fantastic espresso.

Staff are super friendly and coffee is good! Got a flat white worked for a few hours. Great place to WFH... very chill environment, you'll easily find a spot during the week. I'll definitely be stopping in whenever I'm in the neighborhood.
Best (dirty) chai I’ve had in the US. By far.

Been buying coffee beans here for years and I love their beans! I normally order a drink when I come in for a new bag, and while I recommend their coffee and lattes I would steer clear of ordering matcha.

The matcha wasn’t prepared properly and I was handed essentially a cup of milk. There was powder on the sides of the cup but nothing whisked in or mixed and it tasted like milk. I asked if she could add more matcha (expecting her to whisk it with warm water and add like a shot) and instead she added a tiny scoop of powder on top of my iced milk, and seemed annoyed doing so. If you know anything about making powdered drinks, it’s that the powder doesn’t mix especially with ice and it needs to be whisked with warm water. She may just be having an off day, but she’s never particularly welcoming when we’ve come in and she was visibly bothered I said anything about my drink.

Espresso was amazing and the seasonal pour over was interesting and delicious. My wife who can't have dairy really enjoyed her oat milk cortado. Some places burn the oat milk but not here. Staff was very friendly and knowledgeable. The whole place has a nice community feel. Skip the chain coffee for this place every time.

Our espresso machine has held nothing but Enderly beans since we moved to Charlotte, and we are slowly making our way through every kind of bean they offer for our daily coffee. Their Friday home delivery is such an excellent service--every time I run low on beans, I just hop on and pick a new bag to be dropped off at my doorstep for free that Friday--and every time we've been in the shop we are just so pleased by the kindness of those behind the counter. Tony Santoro has personally helped me skip subscription orders if I'm not going through beans as fast and he even helped me exchange a shirt I bought without even having to come in the shop. I'm just so happy a place like this exists in my community and I'm excited to continue to drink Enderly Coffee for years to come.

Service is great and I appreciate the staff’s willingness to help customers with questions about the menu. I know this from eavesdropping, though, because, me? I’m always sure of what I want. I’m boring - but the drinks here aren’t.

Enderly Coffee Co. is quite vibey. It’s full of art and locally made merch such as stone mugs and the like. It’s perfect for catching up with friends, a coffee date, or for studying. It can’t really accommodate big groups so plan accordingly.

Parking is available behind the building but please note that the lot is small. It’s definitely a community gem in an area that is rapidly being gentrified. Somehow, Enderly still feels very Charlotte despite all that’s changing in the neighborhood.

I hope you enjoy it!

reviews_data.review_text: Easily some of the best coffee in charlotte. Always so dense and fresh and full bodied, and super nice baristas. I spend way too much money here!

Enderly Coffee is just a complete gem of Charlotte! Proudly local, hardworking and most importantly: fantastic products. Love their coffee!

I cannot rate the actual brick and mortar Enderly Coffee company because I've never visited the establishment. But I bought a bag of their Honduras Coffee beans from a grocery store and was extremely disappointed. It's honestly the worst Coffee I've ever bought to make at home, especially when I'm grinding the beans fresh myself. It has NO flavor, I even tried using a large amount thinking maybe I didn't use enough, but it didn't matter. It was like drinking warm water with my sweet cream, creamer I adore. That's never happened before.  It's a medium roast and I expected it to be really good considering it's roasted locally in Charlotte.  I moved out of Charlotte in 1985 & I live an hour away. I thought this would be great since Charlotte is so close and should be really fresh and wonderful. Sadly it was not. They may have other Coffee beans that are better and hopefully stronger so it actually tastes like coffee. But I doubt I'll be purchasing this companies products again.  I should have known that when the grocery store marked down all Enderly Coffee products on clearance that apparently weren't selling and I  bet you this is why because it seriously sucks. I threw the rest away because it wasn't worthy salvaging and maybe mixing with other Coffee, because I tried that too. What a waste of money and time. I worked in the restaurant business for 30 yrs and traveled alot as well and this is truly the worst Coffee I've ever had because it doesn't taste like you're drinking coffee at all. And it's not just my opinion, relatives and friends that I had visiting and served it to agreed with me. I was a little embarrassed honestly. I dumped it down the sink and made my other brand  of coffee instead. Very inconvenient when you are serving breakfast to a house full of relatives visiting from out of town.

The place looks nondescript from outside, tucked along several homes turned into small businesses. But once you step inside, it’s very lively and cozy. The staff or friendly. The latte with salted maple was awesome. There is a small parking on the backside. Otherwise you may have to park on the street.

Microwave available to heat up your pastries yourself. Cute place, overall okay.
An awesome roaster. Videos were all time high at their shop and the coffee was outstanding. Loved my espresso! Quiet spot but with great energy - everything roasted in house. Check them out!

Staff are super friendly and coffee is good! Got a flat white worked for a few hours. Great place to WFH... very chill environment, you'll easily find a spot during the week. I'll definitely be stopping in whenever I'm in the neighborhood.
Best (dirty) chai I’ve had in the US. By far.

Been buying coffee beans here for years and I love their beans! I normally order a drink when I come in for a new bag, and while I recommend their coffee and lattes I would steer clear of ordering matcha.

The matcha wasn’t prepared properly and I was handed essentially a cup of milk. There was powder on the sides of the cup but nothing whisked in or mixed and it tasted like milk. I asked if she could add more matcha (expecting her to whisk it with warm water and add like a shot) and instead she added a tiny scoop of powder on top of my iced milk, and seemed annoyed doing so. If you know anything about making powdered drinks, it’s that the powder doesn’t mix especially with ice and it needs to be whisked with warm water. She may just be having an off day, but she’s never particularly welcoming when we’ve come in and she was visibly bothered I said anything about my drink.

Espresso was amazing and the seasonal pour over was interesting and delicious. My wife who can't have dairy really enjoyed her oat milk cortado. Some places burn the oat milk but not here. Staff was very friendly and knowledgeable. The whole place has a nice community feel. Skip the chain coffee for this place every time.

Service is great and I appreciate the staff’s willingness to help customers with questions about the menu. I know this from eavesdropping, though, because, me? I’m always sure of what I want. I’m boring - but the drinks here aren’t.

Enderly Coffee Co. is quite vibey. It’s full of art and locally made merch such as stone mugs and the like. It’s perfect for catching up with friends, a coffee date, or for studying. It can’t really accommodate big groups so plan accordingly.

Parking is available behind the building but please note that the lot is small. It’s definitely a community gem in an area that is rapidly being gentrified. Somehow, Enderly still feels very Charlotte despite all that’s changing in the neighborhood.

I hope you enjoy it!
